com.ibm.team.scm.common

Interface IVersionable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IItem, IItemHandle, IUnmanagedItem, IUnmanagedItemHandle, IVersionableHandle
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IFolder

    public interface IVersionable
extends IVersionableHandle, IUnmanagedItem
    Represents an SCM versionable container type (e.g. file, folder, or symbolic link).

    Since it is an IUnmanagedItem, there is no "current" state. The "current" state is what you have loaded, the after state on a change set, etc. The context may have a versionable that can be considered the "current" state.

    For example, checking in a versionable will create a new state (state_1) for it. The IChange describing the change uses that state as the after state for the versionable, which can be considered the current state from the context of the change set.

    When the versionable is changed and checked in to a new change set, a new state is created (state_2). The IChange uses state_1 as the before state and state_2 as the after state. If another check-in is performed on the same change set, a state_3 may be created to describe the after state. The change set then shows state_1 as the before state and state_3 as the after state. It is not necessary to record state_2 because we are only interested in the versionable state before the change is applied and after the change has been applied.

    See Also:
    IUnmanagedItem

      • getUserProperties

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getUserProperties()
        Returns:
        the properties defined by the user. It does not include the internal versionable implementation properties. The collection of properties returned are not modifiable. The keys and values in this map are considered opaque by the RTC server. URIs should not be placed in this map if the user/caller is expecting these URIs to be portable after data configuration. We do not provide any introspection on these values. This map should not be used for any identifiers which are not immediate attributes of this item. It is not recommended that these fields are used to store references to other items in the repository, as this could impact the state when it gets replicated to another repository.
